result.name: 1+2 豬扒餐廳

reviews.text: A gem in MongKok. Excellent food prepared by award winning chef
Nice dinner but do not really have own style food
Good pork chop but too pricy for a meal

Me & my wife are first time patronize to this restaurant.  It is not obvious when walking along the street but it is a quite nice place for dinner as not many customers, with light music n most important is that the food is tasty and at a good price.  I ordered a fish fillet while my wife ordered their famous pork chop which both taste good n not in small size. I especially delight on their mixed vegetable side dish which is healthy. At busy district like Mongkok, it is a hard-to-find deal and for sure I will come again.

I visit Mong Kok often, and the 1+2 restaurant is consistently good.   The food is both appealing to the local and western pallets.   I've had several dishes on the menu, and the restaurant is known for its pork with tomato sauce.   Try the lemon ice tea.   Prices are very reasonable.

result.name: 1+2 豬扒餐廳 Pork Chop Restaurant

reviews.text: 豬豬排味道唔錯吖😉
在旺角路過一間餐廳，入去諗住食啲嘢，估唔到一間本地餐廳內有星級酒店總廚主理各種不同的食物,味道和擺盆都很好及選用的食材品質都很好。😁😁

食咗至記得影相……
幾好食呀～ 會再幫襯㗎

轉咗手，水準keep唔返。
不過不失。
上碟及味道都不錯，價格合理，坐位不多。
